      <h1>Field Notes</h1>
      <p class="article-date">January 2026</p>
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>
          I carry a small notebook on every trip. Not for planning — for
          noticing. The things that catch my eye rarely survive the journey home
          intact in memory, so I write them down while they are still sharp.
        </p>
        <p>
          A red-tailed hawk circling above a wheat field. The exact shade of
          green where new growth meets dead grass. The sound of wind through dry
          reeds, which is nothing like wind through leaves. These details
          accumulate, and when I look back through old entries, they bring a
          place back to life more vividly than any photograph.
        </p>
        <p>
          The habit has made me a better observer. I notice more now because I
          know I will want to write it down later. Paying attention is a skill,
          and like any skill, it improves with deliberate practice.
        </p>
      </div>
